1
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:07,400
It says it all, doesn't it? Thank you, team.

2
00:00:11,050 --> 00:00:16,350
As we get into our fifth installment this week, studying Lee Strobel's book, The Case for Faith,

3
00:00:18,090 --> 00:00:20,510
with a special guest this morning, Brenda Stuck was here.

4
00:00:20,610 --> 00:00:23,790
That's Mark's sister, and many of you know her, some of you don't,

5
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:26,230
and it's just great to have kind of family playing together this morning.

6
00:00:26,330 --> 00:00:29,190
So, Brenda, wherever you are, we're glad that you're here. Welcome.

7
00:00:30,690 --> 00:00:31,890
Well, let's get right into this.

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Take a look at this statement from Rabbi, I'm going to say this right, Shmuley Boteach.

9
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:42,600
I am absolutely against any religion

10
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:45,760
that says that one faith is superior to another.

11
00:00:46,630 --> 00:00:48,650
I don't see how that is anything different

12
00:00:48,650 --> 00:00:50,470
from spiritual racism.

13
00:00:51,630 --> 00:00:54,850
It's a way of saying that we are closer to God than you,

14
00:00:54,850 --> 00:00:56,490
and that's what leads to hatred.

15
00:00:58,380 --> 00:00:59,160
Strong statement.

16
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:02,800
Let's take a look at something else.

17
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:04,080
R.C. Sproul, theologian,

18
00:01:04,780 --> 00:01:07,500
said something in completely contradistinction to that.

19
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:08,140
He said,

20
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:10,300
Moses could mediate on the law.

21
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:13,190
Muhammad could brandish a sword.

22
00:01:13,950 --> 00:01:15,470
Buddha could give personal counsel.

23
00:01:15,850 --> 00:01:17,990
Confucius could offer wise sayings.

24
00:01:18,410 --> 00:01:23,350
But none of these men were qualified to offer an atonement for the sins of the world.

25
00:01:23,770 --> 00:01:28,090
Christ alone is worthy of unlimited devotion and service.

26
00:01:30,010 --> 00:01:32,430
Boy, two worldviews coming in a collision course.

27
00:01:32,530 --> 00:01:33,350
Can't you just see that?

28
00:01:34,860 --> 00:01:38,980
Two radically different perspectives on this Jesus and the nature of truth.

29
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:41,060
And those are the topics we're going to look at this morning.

30
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:47,530
What is it really about Jesus, and what is it about truth that people are so uncomfortable

31
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:48,270
with today?

32
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:55,180
What you heard in those two statements, of course, is just a complete clash of worldviews.

33
00:01:55,540 --> 00:02:00,180
One is saying that one religion is true and others are false, and some people don't like

34
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:00,520
that.

35
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:06,340
The other one is saying there's something so radical about Jesus that he's worthy of

36
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:07,460
all worship and praise.

37
00:02:09,740 --> 00:02:14,180
Let me share with you this morning, and you've already heard it, I think the most outrageous,

38
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:21,360
exclusive, narrow-minded, non-politically correct phrases ever uttered, and you already

39
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:29,700
heard it. You ready? Take a look. I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one can come

40
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:43,990
to the Father except through me. Who does Jesus think he is to say that? God. That's

41
00:02:43,990 --> 00:02:51,190
inflammatory talk. In some circles, those are fighting words. That is so narrow-minded. That

42
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:59,230
is so limiting. That is so non-tolerant. How dare he say something like that? He's a spiritual

43
00:02:59,230 --> 00:03:10,510
racist. He thinks his franchise is better than all the rest. Now, where does he get off saying

44
00:03:10,510 --> 00:03:17,330
stuff like that? And you will hear language like that. How dare anybody say something like that?

45
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:22,390
And how dare you, as a follower of him, make those kinds of claims?

46
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:27,240
In fact, Indian philosopher Swami Vivekananda, if I've said that right,

47
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:30,020
said in 1893 to the World Parliament of Religions,

48
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:32,440
and that, by the way, is a real Swami right there,

49
00:03:33,930 --> 00:03:36,790
he said, we accept all religions as true.

50
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:42,630
And then later in that conference, it's reported that he said

51
00:03:42,630 --> 00:03:46,610
that the real sin is to call somebody else a sinner.

52
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,700
Interesting.

53
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,940
Now, in our culture today, we are extremely relativistic.

54
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:54,080
We've talked about this a lot.

55
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:56,640
There's really no sense of right and wrong in our culture.

56
00:03:57,420 --> 00:04:01,200
There's no sense that there's a truth for all peoples at all time.

57
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:04,240
And yet I would also say that in the past six weeks,

58
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:07,220
we have seen events that are beginning to challenge those notions

59
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:09,520
of a sense of universal right and wrong,

60
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:11,600
and we are struggling to wrestle with those issues.

61
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,660
But I want to say something this morning as we begin looking at Jesus

62
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:16,280
about the nature of truth.

63
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:20,540
because truth by nature is exclusive.

64
00:04:21,820 --> 00:04:22,780
Do you know what I mean by that?

65
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,400
That truth by nature is exclusive.

66
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:27,900
If something is true, then something else is not true.

67
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:31,230
My Bible is black.

68
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:32,490
It's all black.

69
00:04:32,590 --> 00:04:35,470
The whole thing has been dyed or painted or whatever it is,

70
00:04:35,690 --> 00:04:36,970
and therefore it is not yellow.

71
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,020
It is black.

72
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,000
You can claim it's yellow.

73
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,040
You can say it's yellow,

74
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:43,900
and you can be open-minded and believe it's yellow,

75
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,620
but the truth is it's black, and it's not yellow.

76
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:49,440
So we've excluded yellow, we've excluded red,

77
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,680
we've excluded gray, and some other colors.

78
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:53,880
And I'm sorry if that's not politically correct,

79
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:54,860
but this is black.

80
00:04:58,140 --> 00:04:59,080
It can't be both.

81
00:05:00,490 --> 00:05:02,290
And we live in a world that bristles

82
00:05:02,290 --> 00:05:04,090
with that kind of objectivism.

83
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:06,710
We bristle in a world that says that certain things are true.

84
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:09,610
But you know, in some ways, we don't live like that, really.

85
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,290
When you take one occupation, you exclude others.

86
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,360
When you finally settle on one spouse,

87
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,360
you exclude the other potentials out there.

88
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:20,810
I mean, we do those kinds of things all the time.

89
00:05:20,810 --> 00:05:25,350
When it comes to faith issues, we really do want to go to the church.

90
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:30,120
Because for some reason, in that realm, the spiritual realm,

91
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,040
we don't want to submit to truth.

92
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:34,520
We want to kind of truly have it our way.

93
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:44,820
I think because one of the reasons we do that is because deep down,

94
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:48,960
I'm not convinced that people really believe that any of those faiths really are true.

95
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:53,460
I think we tend to look at faith and religions

96
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:56,280
as kind of a coping mechanism that helps you get by.

97
00:05:57,280 --> 00:06:00,040
And so therefore, it doesn't really matter what you choose

98
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,500
as long as it works for you

99
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,740
and certain practices get you through the day.

100
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,160
It doesn't really matter.

101
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,120
So let's just assume they're all true

102
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,000
and kind of move on to some other issue.

103
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:11,750
I think that's kind of one of the underlying issues.

104
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:14,110
The problem is, as we're seeing, friends,

105
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:15,550
ideas have consequences.

106
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:20,090
That our ideas are not just held in some kind of vacuum,

107
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:23,350
that ideas have consequences in the real world.

108
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:28,140
And I think it's important to understand at the same time

109
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:31,660
that other religions are not all one big soup

110
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:34,280
and that they all make sense and you can sort of integrate them all.

111
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:37,280
In fact, I would say that they are also very exclusive

112
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:39,660
if you really get into the teachings of them.

113
00:06:41,020 --> 00:06:43,060
There's a common misconception out there today

114
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:45,480
that all religions basically teach the same thing.

115
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,780
It doesn't really matter what you believe

116
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:48,700
as long as you're sincere.

117
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:50,360
They all are basically the same,

118
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:51,900
and the basic two tenets are this,

119
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:53,680
the universal fatherhood of God

120
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,100
and the universal brotherhood of human beings.

121
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:58,980
That's basically underneath all the religions.

122
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,400
Well, I want to say this, A, as my first point,

123
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,260
that the other religions are exclusive

124
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:05,500
because they don't all teach the same thing,

125
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:08,500
and if it's one way, it's not another way.

126
00:07:09,590 --> 00:07:10,870
In the book we're looking at,

127
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:13,710
Dr. Ravi Zacharias is interviewed by Lee Strobel,

128
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:15,870
and he makes the comment that

129
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:20,810
only people who don't understand other religions would say that they all teach the same thing.

130
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:28,040
So when you hear that misconception, and I've heard it a lot, in fact, I would say people use

131
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:32,100
it as a way to kind of just blow off the conversation, let's move it to something else.

132
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:36,640
They all teach the same thing, let's move on. It kind of shuts down the argument, doesn't it?

133
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:42,870
But he's saying that only a person who doesn't know anything about them would even make that

134
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:46,630
comment. So when you're sitting there across the barbecue and you're moving the ribs back and

135
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:49,790
forth, you're talking to friends and neighbors and family, and somebody says, well, you know,

136
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:55,730
they all teach basically the same thing. You can gently say, actually, they don't. And have you

137
00:07:55,730 --> 00:07:59,890
actually looked at each one? And you might consider reading some of the writings from each one,

138
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:06,210
because they're very different. Let me give you some examples. How can a Buddhist claim

139
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:11,290
that their faith teaches the universal fatherhood of God, when their faith doesn't even claim there

140
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:19,720
is a God. We've got a problem. Same thing with Confucianism. Confucianism is basically

141
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:25,460
a philosophy of life more than it is a true religion, and there really is no God in Confucianism

142
00:08:25,460 --> 00:08:31,390
either. Those do not teach the same thing as all religions right away. How can a Hindu

143
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:35,210
claim that their faith teaches the universal fatherhood of God when their faith claims

144
00:08:35,210 --> 00:08:43,850
that you basically are part of God? Cliff Kinectley, who's an author and a speaker, says

145
00:08:43,850 --> 00:08:49,790
this. It says, the Bhagavad Gita, the Upanishads, and other books of Eastern mysticism all teach

146
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:54,610
that God is one. Everything is God. You are God. I am God. The tree is God. Good is God.

147
00:08:54,690 --> 00:09:00,510
Evil is God. Basically, all those things are God. Therefore, God is impersonal. Therefore,

148
00:09:00,610 --> 00:09:05,640
if he's impersonal, he's not your father. So see the problem again. When you look at

149
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:11,090
these things carefully, they don't all teach the same thing. So is God one and we're all

150
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:16,710
part of God, or is he separate? And you really can't have it both ways. He's either an impersonal

151
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:24,000
force, or he's a personal creator. And to sort of blend them all together is really intellectual

152
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:30,200
nonsense. But our culture doesn't want to talk about that. It just wants to move along. It works

153
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:39,400
for you. Great. Now, the brotherhood of all people. The only reason we can say that is because we

154
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:45,240
believe that there's a creator that's made us in his image. But if you don't have a creator concept,

155
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,940
then it doesn't mean anything to say we're all in the same brotherhood of humanity.

156
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:52,280
And different religions have different concepts of creation.

157
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:55,720
Like we talked about, some don't even believe we're separate from the creation.

158
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:58,780
God and we and the creation are all together one.

159
00:09:59,860 --> 00:10:02,700
So right away we have differences on the brotherhood of human beings.

160
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:07,220
We have differences in the concept of God as Father.

161
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:10,130
Here's one thing to remember.

162
00:10:10,530 --> 00:10:15,230
All the religions except Christianity teach basically the concept.

163
00:10:15,230 --> 00:10:16,410
Here's where they are similar.

164
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:20,570
they basically say you have to get your act together to get to God.

165
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:25,600
That you've got to somehow do something, go through a certain system,

166
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:30,900
pray certain prayers, rotate a wheel, don't eat these foods,

167
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:32,680
take off these days and not work,

168
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:37,060
all these different things to kind of work your way into God's presence.

169
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:40,480
Pray five times a day, you name it, you've got to do things,

170
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:43,300
get your act together, and then God will accept you.

171
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:45,960
That's where they're similar.

172
00:10:47,130 --> 00:10:49,250
They all offer different ways of doing that,

173
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:50,590
but there's the similarity.

174
00:10:51,010 --> 00:10:52,970
However, Christianity is totally different

175
00:10:52,970 --> 00:10:55,830
because Christianity says that we're never going to earn a right

176
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:57,710
to get into the relationship with a holy God,

177
00:10:58,150 --> 00:10:59,450
that we can never be good enough,

178
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:00,830
that we're already broken and in sin,

179
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:02,930
but God has taken the initiative

180
00:11:02,930 --> 00:11:06,950
and that God has done something through Jesus Christ,

181
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:10,990
who is God in the flesh, to bring us to himself.

182
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:13,550
And that, friends, is radically different.

183
00:11:14,970 --> 00:11:15,670
Radically different.

184
00:11:18,810 --> 00:11:20,530
Now, does that mean that other religions

185
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:21,450
don't have some truth?

186
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:22,950
Absolutely.

187
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,970
There's great ethical teaching in many of the religions.

188
00:11:26,410 --> 00:11:28,030
You'll notice shades of Jesus' teaching

189
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:29,310
in a number of different places,

190
00:11:29,570 --> 00:11:31,570
and I would say they have elements of the truth.

191
00:11:31,970 --> 00:11:34,530
But I would say they don't have truth, capital T.

192
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:36,840
And we'll come to that in a few minutes,

193
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:37,820
why I think that's true.

194
00:11:41,510 --> 00:11:43,330
Second thing, why Jesus now?

195
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:46,020
Jesus answers the issues.

196
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,580
Lee Strobel, as he's continuing to talk

197
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:49,580
with Ravi Zacharias,

198
00:11:50,930 --> 00:11:53,770
Ravi brings out four interesting concepts

199
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:56,110
that all religions are trying to work with

200
00:11:56,110 --> 00:11:58,710
and questions that all religions try and deal with.

201
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:01,910
And he's saying that Jesus is the most consistent answer

202
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:04,670
for all the questions, and there's a coherence.

203
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:07,110
There's a sense where in Christianity, it's coherent,

204
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:10,870
it makes sense, and it seems to validate reality.

205
00:12:11,610 --> 00:12:14,770
When you look at the world, you say, yeah, these things work.

206
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:17,750
First one is the issue of origins.

207
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:20,230
And we've talked about this in the past few messages.

208
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:24,230
Kind of the concept, where do we come from and who are we as human beings?

209
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:27,570
The Eastern faiths say that we are part of God.

210
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:34,560
And if you kind of wake up spiritually and realize that, you can be part of God in some way.

211
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:39,120
And the challenge there is to say that you just haven't woken up to the reality that you're God.

212
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:43,170
But you know, deep down, I don't think we believe that.

213
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:46,920
I think you and I all know that when you get really honest, we're not God.

214
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:49,040
In fact, I would say we're alienated from God.

215
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:56,000
Christianity says we're creatures created by God.

216
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:58,640
with a will and we can choose good and evil

217
00:12:58,640 --> 00:13:01,310
and that we have broken moral boundaries

218
00:13:01,310 --> 00:13:03,950
and we need to be brought back to God.

219
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,360
It says we're separated from God.

220
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:09,780
And you know, I think our existential experience

221
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:10,780
would validate that.

222
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,000
Jesus taught that.

223
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:14,280
And in Jesus, he's the one who brought us back

224
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:15,660
to the Lord himself.

225
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,560
That's the origins issue.

226
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,980
I'm sorry, I'll add one more thing.

227
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,480
Jesus says this in Mark 2.17.

228
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:23,680
Take a look at this.

229
00:13:24,340 --> 00:13:26,000
Healthy people don't need a doctor.

230
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,200
Sick people do.

231
00:13:27,860 --> 00:13:30,840
I've come to call sinners and not those who think they're already good enough.

232
00:13:32,610 --> 00:13:33,550
Friends, we're all sick.

233
00:13:34,810 --> 00:13:35,490
We need a Savior.

234
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:39,500
The second thing is the issue of meaning.

235
00:13:41,930 --> 00:13:45,970
Jesus said we're to love God with our heart and our soul and our mind.

236
00:13:46,690 --> 00:13:49,510
And then we're to love our neighbors as ourselves.

237
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:53,600
If you worship God with all of your heart, soul, and mind,

238
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:57,000
if you spend time in worship in a love relationship with God,

239
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,540
that is an extremely centering experience.

240
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:05,940
It is one that will empower you to have more love, to love other people.

241
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:08,540
It's in worship that we find meaning.

242
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:11,440
We find ourselves in the right relationship with God

243
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:15,880
as the creatures giving back adoration that we were created for to begin with.

244
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,260
It fits with the way our souls were created.

245
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:21,920
It makes sense and allows us to love other people

246
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:24,280
when we find meaning in worship.

247
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:29,460
The third thing that religions try and deal with, and the questions are,

248
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:31,420
is where is the source of morality?

249
00:14:33,740 --> 00:14:35,120
Contrary to popular myth,

250
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:37,140
morality is not based in the culture.

251
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,600
It's based in the very character of a holy God.

252
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:44,940
Because where do we get the universal notions

253
00:14:44,940 --> 00:14:45,740
of right and wrong?

254
00:14:46,180 --> 00:14:48,060
Where do we as people across the globe

255
00:14:48,060 --> 00:14:50,240
have these deep-rooted understandings

256
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,840
that some things are right and some things are wrong?

257
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,140
If they're based on culture,

258
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,860
they should be all completely different.

259
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:58,580
In our intellect, we're trying in today's culture

260
00:14:58,580 --> 00:14:59,760
to make that case.

261
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:02,680
But I think we're denying the deeper realities

262
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,740
that we all are made in the image of God

263
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:08,200
and have broken his moral framework that he set up.

264
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:14,120
Christianity has an explanation for where morality comes from.

265
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:17,460
The Bible says that God wrote it on our hearts

266
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:21,100
because he's the one who defines it to begin with.

267
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:24,350
The fourth one is the issue of destiny.

268
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:27,070
Different faiths have different interpretations

269
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:30,690
and concepts of what happens for our ultimate destiny,

270
00:15:30,690 --> 00:15:33,290
the eternal life, the afterlife, and all those things.

271
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:41,560
the destiny issue is inherently bound up in christianity in history it's not bound up just

272
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:46,500
in some mythical idea that can be created by anybody and written down it's based in historical

273
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:52,100
reality that jesus lived on earth lived the perfect life performed miracles and then died

274
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:58,620
and rose again and gives us the power through himself to have eternal life forever and he's

275
00:15:58,620 --> 00:16:05,150
been to the other side and back. Our destiny is rooted in Jesus' actions on earth and

276
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:09,030
his promises. Other faiths don't have that kind of experience. Where else do you have

277
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:15,590
a figure in any other religion that can claim to have died and come back and been proven

278
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:21,490
historically to be true? It's not there. Buddha is in the grave. Muhammad is in the

279
00:16:21,490 --> 00:16:29,750
grave. Confucius is in the grave. You get the idea. Jesus, not in the grave. That's

280
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,790
why destiny is bound up in Jesus.

281
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,140
Now, I think about Jesus,

282
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,020
about that nature of truth in his life

283
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:39,140
and his teachings. They square

284
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:41,140
with reality. It's also interesting that you can do a

285
00:16:41,140 --> 00:16:42,760
logic tree, and this was not my idea.

286
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,160
C.S. Lewis comes up with this, and it's so

287
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:47,140
brilliant. Many of you have seen this, and I want to share it with you

288
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:50,000
again. But here's why Jesus.

289
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,060
Jesus claims to be God.

290
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:54,260
Outrageous statement.

291
00:16:56,220 --> 00:16:57,020
If he's wrong

292
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:58,900
and it's false,

293
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:00,600
then you have one of two choices.

294
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,980
He either knew it was false, and

295
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:09,820
therefore he's a liar and a bad guy because he taught a lot of things and he said a lot of things

296
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:15,080
and he started a movement and yet deep down he knew he was pulling the wool over their eyes

297
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:26,140
and that makes him a liar and a bad man or he's simply a lunatic he claims to be god and he's just

298
00:17:26,140 --> 00:17:32,180
mentally ill i mean he thinks he's god does he well that's interesting you know we've got a padded

299
00:17:32,180 --> 00:17:42,480
room for you, okay? It's one of those two if it's false. He either knows that he's lying when he

300
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:50,010
says he's God, or he doesn't know he's lying and he's just out there and he's a lunatic, or if it's

301
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:57,940
true, then he is Lord and he's what he says he is. And if he's what he says he is, that's a radical

302
00:17:57,940 --> 00:18:03,700
statement that we have to deal with. Oh my goodness, if Jesus is God, then whatever he says goes.

303
00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:07,430
So really for us, we have to sort of work that through.

304
00:18:08,490 --> 00:18:11,370
If you think he's a lunatic, it becomes on your head to prove

305
00:18:11,370 --> 00:18:12,810
why you think he was insane.

306
00:18:15,850 --> 00:18:18,090
Or if he's a liar, you need to look at that angle.

307
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:23,220
I would say that the evidence points to him being Lord

308
00:18:23,220 --> 00:18:30,140
because his life, his teachings, his miracles,

309
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:33,360
the prophecies about him, all fulfilled,

310
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:38,480
his death and his resurrection all point to the Lord column

311
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:40,120
and not the other two.

312
00:18:40,740 --> 00:18:44,600
People can claim that they can be God, and they can die, and that's the end.

313
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:48,780
But when you claim to be God, perform miracles, and come back from the dead and say,

314
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:51,270
you see, I've been there and I'm back.

315
00:18:52,580 --> 00:18:53,120
He's God.

316
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:59,160
And so when Jesus says he's the way and the truth and the life,

317
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:04,730
we have to pause and say, wow, if that's true,

318
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:09,500
then my life needs to come under that direction.

319
00:19:11,810 --> 00:19:16,170
You see, it's only outrageous, it's only narrow-minded,

320
00:19:16,170 --> 00:19:20,690
it's only politically incorrect if it's not true.

321
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,780
Because then he is just being a spiritual racist.

322
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:28,420
But if he is indeed God, he has every right to say that.

323
00:19:28,860 --> 00:19:30,980
And he has every right to call us to accountability.

324
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:34,440
He's got every right to do whatever he wants to do because he's God.

325
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:39,760
It's only when it's not true that it becomes a problem.

326
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:44,320
But friends, if it is true that Jesus is the way, the truth, and the life,

327
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:47,620
we need to come under that and respect that and respond to that.

328
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:51,600
And I hope you'll come to that place of realizing that it's true.

329
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,500
The question will come up across the barbecue

330
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:58,740
as you're talking to a friend or family.

331
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:03,050
Well, if Jesus is the only way, what about those who've never heard?

332
00:20:03,970 --> 00:20:06,310
If that message is the only way to salvation,

333
00:20:06,710 --> 00:20:09,690
what about the people that never get a missionary in town,

334
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:11,810
that never hear it on the radio, don't have a TV or whatever?

335
00:20:12,790 --> 00:20:13,610
What about those people?

336
00:20:14,430 --> 00:20:15,210
That's a good question.

337
00:20:15,470 --> 00:20:18,150
And Paul was actually wrestling with that implication

338
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:20,010
when he wrote these words in Romans 10.13.

339
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:20,770
He writes,

340
00:20:20,770 --> 00:20:24,110
for anyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

341
00:20:24,980 --> 00:20:27,600
But how can they call on him to save them unless they believe in him?

342
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:30,300
And how can they believe in him if they've never heard about him?

343
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:33,340
And how can they hear about him unless someone tells them?

344
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,560
And so, you know, from texts like this, we get the mandate

345
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:38,620
that we're supposed to be out there telling people,

346
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:42,020
because he raises that question, how are they going to know unless we tell them?

347
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:47,590
And we are challenged by Jesus to bring the message of Jesus Christ

348
00:20:47,590 --> 00:20:51,550
to all the peoples in all the nations of all the tribes

349
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,970
with all the different languages,

350
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:56,070
we must bring that truth to people.

351
00:20:56,510 --> 00:20:58,910
For there they will find meaning and purpose

352
00:20:58,910 --> 00:21:01,210
and forgiveness and eternal life.

353
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:04,000
And it's the only place you're going to find it.

354
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,160
You won't get it in the church.

355
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:07,490
You won't get it in other faiths.

356
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:12,050
You find all those things in Jesus Christ and Him alone.

357
00:21:13,530 --> 00:21:14,790
Jesus said in Matthew 29,

358
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:18,390
Therefore go and make disciples of all the nations,

359
00:21:19,230 --> 00:21:21,230
baptizing them in the name of the Father

360
00:21:21,230 --> 00:21:24,030
and of the Son and the Holy Spirit.

361
00:21:24,670 --> 00:21:25,990
And we've seen that today.

362
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:31,910
Paul makes an interesting statement, though,

363
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:36,760
about the creation as a tool in pointing to Christ.

364
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,760
In Romans 1.20, the Bible says,

365
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,260
from the time the world was created,

366
00:21:41,780 --> 00:21:43,620
people have seen the earth and the sky

367
00:21:43,620 --> 00:21:44,860
and all that God made.

368
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,560
They can clearly see his invisible qualities,

369
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,340
his eternal power and divine nature.

370
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,800
So they have no excuse whatsoever for not knowing God.

371
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:53,780
Isn't that interesting?

372
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,300
He's saying that the creation itself

373
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:58,300
is a pointer that points you to God himself.

374
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:01,040
And we are challenged to come alongside and say,

375
00:22:01,140 --> 00:22:03,820
you see what you're pointing to is the one who is the creator,

376
00:22:04,620 --> 00:22:07,140
the one who says the way, the truth, and the life.

377
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:11,270
It's also instructive to realize that God is sovereign

378
00:22:11,270 --> 00:22:13,170
over peoples and places and time.

379
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:15,110
The Bible says in Acts 17,

380
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:19,300
from one man he created all the nations throughout the whole earth.

381
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:22,200
He decided beforehand which should rise and fall,

382
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:24,000
and he determined their boundaries.

383
00:22:24,620 --> 00:22:28,200
His purpose in all of this was that the nations should seek after God

384
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:30,380
and perhaps feel their way toward him and find him,

385
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,700
though he's not far from any one of us.

386
00:22:34,060 --> 00:22:34,940
Friends, I want to say this.

387
00:22:35,060 --> 00:22:40,340
We are responsible as God's people to fulfill our part of God's program.

388
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:44,980
We are challenged to bring that message to all people as much as possible,

389
00:22:44,980 --> 00:22:47,840
and he's invested that charge to us.

390
00:22:48,580 --> 00:22:52,100
It is up to God to judge those that have not heard that message,

391
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,300
for God is the judge of all peoples anyway.

392
00:22:54,580 --> 00:22:57,380
But I do know this from the character of the God revealed in Scripture

393
00:22:57,380 --> 00:23:02,340
and from Him I personally know that God is just

394
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:07,110
and God's judgment is perfect and just.

395
00:23:07,890 --> 00:23:10,630
I don't have an answer for how all that works

396
00:23:10,630 --> 00:23:12,910
because we're talking about a God outside of space and time

397
00:23:12,910 --> 00:23:15,190
and He can put people in different times and eras

398
00:23:15,190 --> 00:23:16,950
and all that is a huge mystery.

399
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:19,630
But I'm here to say that if He is outside of 11 dimensions,

400
00:23:19,990 --> 00:23:21,810
He can work out who's going to hear and who's not

401
00:23:21,810 --> 00:23:22,490
and He already knows.

402
00:23:22,590 --> 00:23:24,650
I mean, that's way beyond our ability to understand

403
00:23:24,650 --> 00:23:27,450
and all I know is he's challenged me to share the message,

404
00:23:27,730 --> 00:23:29,910
and if he's got me, his beat on me,

405
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:31,530
to present it to this friend,

406
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:34,090
then I've got to be there to do it

407
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:36,850
and let him take care of the rest.

408
00:23:39,870 --> 00:23:41,890
If we're to be involved in that kind of program

409
00:23:41,890 --> 00:23:44,350
to present this truth, my final point is,

410
00:23:44,570 --> 00:23:46,430
then what's our attitude then for our arguments?

411
00:23:47,330 --> 00:23:49,390
Because one of the things that becomes a real turnoff

412
00:23:49,390 --> 00:23:51,090
for people as they're talking about truth

413
00:23:51,090 --> 00:23:52,890
is this issue of the attitude.

414
00:23:53,150 --> 00:23:56,110
Talking about truth requires a certain level of maturity.

415
00:23:56,110 --> 00:23:59,070
because of the exclusive nature of truth.

416
00:24:00,910 --> 00:24:04,790
People can get really emotionally in turmoil over these issues,

417
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:07,490
especially when you're saying to somebody

418
00:24:07,490 --> 00:24:10,090
that a path that they have followed, a set of teachings,

419
00:24:10,470 --> 00:24:12,310
may not be the total truth.

420
00:24:12,470 --> 00:24:14,410
That's very offensive in our culture.

421
00:24:14,410 --> 00:24:17,830
And we have to be mature and wise in how we present that

422
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:21,080
because truth presented with the wrong attitude

423
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:25,130
comes across as smug or as arrogant.

424
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,610
and we're trying to be loving

425
00:24:27,610 --> 00:24:28,590
and tell people the truth

426
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:30,310
but it sometimes can come across

427
00:24:30,310 --> 00:24:32,600
as really distasteful

428
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,840
and a real turn off for people

429
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:36,820
who are interested in investigating truth.

430
00:24:38,420 --> 00:24:40,260
So how we present that truth is important.

431
00:24:41,780 --> 00:24:42,820
Now I realize for some of you

432
00:24:42,820 --> 00:24:43,640
you're hearing this concept

433
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,340
you're saying but you know

434
00:24:44,340 --> 00:24:45,260
truth is truth is truth

435
00:24:45,260 --> 00:24:46,760
it doesn't matter how I say it

436
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:47,860
as long as it's said

437
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:49,300
deal with it, right?

438
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,260
And that's true

439
00:24:51,260 --> 00:24:52,360
I mean truth is truth, right?

440
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:52,960
I mean it is.

441
00:24:54,350 --> 00:24:55,750
But in a culture that's interested

442
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:57,850
more about the haircut of a politician

443
00:24:57,850 --> 00:24:59,590
over what they stand for,

444
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:02,140
we've got to be sensitive.

445
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:05,230
You can say truth is truth is truth

446
00:25:05,230 --> 00:25:06,570
and you deal with it and that's it.

447
00:25:06,870 --> 00:25:09,150
But you know, that's not a loving thing to do.

448
00:25:09,910 --> 00:25:10,810
You're saying truth,

449
00:25:10,890 --> 00:25:13,370
but how you say truth is important as well.

450
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:16,790
I think we need to listen to that.

451
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,800
Mahatma Gandhi said this,

452
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:22,000
I like their Christ.

453
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:24,040
I don't like their Christians.

454
00:25:26,290 --> 00:25:29,220
That's kind of ugly, isn't it?

455
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:33,590
Friedrich Nietzsche, a philosopher, said this,

456
00:25:34,430 --> 00:25:35,610
I will believe in the Redeemer

457
00:25:35,610 --> 00:25:37,510
when the Christian looks a little more redeemed.

458
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:41,850
Kind of ouch, huh?

459
00:25:42,740 --> 00:25:42,960
Yeah.

460
00:25:43,260 --> 00:25:45,720
You have the truth, but how we communicate that truth

461
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,640
and how we live out that truth

462
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:49,780
is as important as getting it out there.

463
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:53,020
So once again, our message needs to be consistent

464
00:25:53,020 --> 00:25:55,440
with our walk and our talk

465
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:58,580
and how we operate with people in the world.

466
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,320
Those are insightful comments,

467
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:01,560
and I think we need to hear those.

468
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:03,380
And you know, Peter said some similar things.

469
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,760
In 1 Peter chapter 3, he said,

470
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:07,800
You must worship Christ as Lord of your life.

471
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:10,060
And if you are asked about your Christian hope,

472
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,020
always be ready to explain it.

473
00:26:12,060 --> 00:26:12,700
Now listen to this.

474
00:26:13,060 --> 00:26:14,740
But you must do this in a what?

475
00:26:14,940 --> 00:26:17,760
In a gentle and respectful way.

476
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,180
And there's the clincher for us.

477
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:25,420
If you've got truth, you can slap people around with it,

478
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:28,710
or you can present it in a way that they can hear it

479
00:26:28,710 --> 00:26:30,970
that is gentle and respectful.

480
00:26:30,970 --> 00:26:34,880
because whether a person has a false doctrine

481
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:35,780
about a different religion,

482
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,640
they are still made in God's image.

483
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:40,120
God has given them a brain and an intellect and a soul

484
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,640
and he wants them to know truth

485
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:43,160
and he wants to use you and me

486
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:45,960
and we've got to do it in a respectful and loving way.

487
00:26:49,940 --> 00:26:52,380
We need to do it with grace and with respect.

488
00:26:53,370 --> 00:26:54,350
Now, let's recap for a minute.

489
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:56,560
I hope I've made the case

490
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,780
that all religions do not teach the same thing.

491
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,000
And if you don't believe me, which is fine,

492
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,720
but go to the books, go to the original teachers

493
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:05,620
and begin to ferret this out for yourself

494
00:27:05,620 --> 00:27:06,840
because you need to understand

495
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:08,280
that they are not all the same.

496
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,240
And when somebody tries to say,

497
00:27:10,580 --> 00:27:11,720
oh, it doesn't matter what you believe,

498
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:13,180
just be sincere, they're all the same,

499
00:27:13,220 --> 00:27:14,800
you need to say, no, wait a second,

500
00:27:14,860 --> 00:27:15,660
let's really look at that

501
00:27:15,660 --> 00:27:16,860
because they're not all the same.

502
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:18,440
In fact, they're very different.

503
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,860
Jesus is exclusive.

504
00:27:22,260 --> 00:27:24,120
Other religions are exclusive.

505
00:27:24,820 --> 00:27:26,840
So if we're going to claim truth and be exclusive,

506
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:29,720
the challenge is, are we standing on the right one?

507
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:31,160
Why Jesus?

508
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:33,960
Because his life validates his ministry

509
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,160
and his identity as God.

510
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:40,120
His miracles validate his identity as God.

511
00:27:41,220 --> 00:27:43,900
His teachings, and you'll notice the scriptures

512
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:45,460
talk about him teaching with an authority

513
00:27:45,460 --> 00:27:47,000
that's beyond this world,

514
00:27:47,860 --> 00:27:50,360
with a power that's beyond anything they've ever seen,

515
00:27:50,660 --> 00:27:52,940
with wisdom beyond anything ever experienced.

516
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:54,920
His teachings validate his identity.

517
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:59,240
And finally, his resurrection validates his identity.

518
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:02,300
He said he would be killed

519
00:28:02,300 --> 00:28:03,680
and he would rise again on the third day,

520
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,140
and that's what happened.

521
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,000
Jesus is either a liar

522
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,800
or a lunatic

523
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:12,780
or he's Lord.

524
00:28:16,780 --> 00:28:18,340
I don't know how else to work that out.

525
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:23,160
We've shared the message of Christianity

526
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,520
answers for the questions

527
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:26,160
that religions are trying to wrestle with.

528
00:28:27,090 --> 00:28:28,510
And so I'm here after all of that

529
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:29,470
to say boldly

530
00:28:29,470 --> 00:28:31,290
that Jesus said it first

531
00:28:31,290 --> 00:28:33,810
but Jesus is the only way to God.

532
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,300
It's the way that God

533
00:28:36,300 --> 00:28:37,360
of the universe

534
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:39,900
decided to bring people to himself.

535
00:28:41,940 --> 00:28:43,020
If it's not true

536
00:28:43,020 --> 00:28:45,040
that is a spiritually racist comment.

537
00:28:46,300 --> 00:28:48,460
It is non-politically correct.

538
00:28:49,140 --> 00:28:50,080
It's outrageous.

539
00:28:51,060 --> 00:28:53,160
It's just, it's ridiculous.

540
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:55,340
Or it's true.

541
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:57,240
And if it's true,

542
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:58,620
then we need to make sure our lives

543
00:28:58,620 --> 00:29:00,260
come under his authority.

544
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:02,400
And so my final conclusion is this.

545
00:29:02,780 --> 00:29:06,330
Where do you stand with Jesus' bold claims?

546
00:29:08,570 --> 00:29:10,010
Where do you stand with those claims?

547
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:11,130
Do you reject them?

548
00:29:11,570 --> 00:29:12,750
And if you do, why?

549
00:29:13,730 --> 00:29:14,650
Or do you embrace them?

550
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:18,400
And if you do, how are you doing in your walk with Jesus today?

551
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:20,660
Where do you stand with his bold claims?

552
00:29:21,300 --> 00:29:25,300
If you are reluctant to believe, my challenge would be this.

553
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:27,580
Is your reluctance to believe, is it intellectual?

554
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:30,840
Or is it simply a matter of the will?

555
00:29:32,650 --> 00:29:35,030
Is it you have not seen enough evidence, and that's fine,

556
00:29:35,070 --> 00:29:36,410
and we can present that to you?

557
00:29:36,410 --> 00:29:39,030
Or is it you've seen all the evidence, you know it's true,

558
00:29:39,330 --> 00:29:41,470
but you don't want to go there?

559
00:29:42,510 --> 00:29:44,670
You simply don't want to change your life,

560
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:47,130
you simply don't want to go through the experience

561
00:29:47,130 --> 00:29:49,810
of embracing Jesus as Lord for different reasons.

562
00:29:50,030 --> 00:29:51,390
But it's an issue of the will.

563
00:29:51,910 --> 00:29:54,230
It's on your head and not because of the evidence.

564
00:29:54,590 --> 00:29:56,270
It's something you don't want to do.

565
00:29:58,480 --> 00:29:59,420
And then I would say this,

566
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:01,360
what more do you need to know

567
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:03,750
or what more do you need to do

568
00:30:03,750 --> 00:30:06,880
before you give your life to Jesus Christ?

569
00:30:08,950 --> 00:30:10,150
And I really want to challenge us

570
00:30:10,150 --> 00:30:11,450
to be intellectually consistent here.

571
00:30:12,230 --> 00:30:13,810
If I can just have you hold on for a second.

572
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:14,590
I know it's warm in here

573
00:30:14,590 --> 00:30:16,090
and it's been a long morning,

574
00:30:16,190 --> 00:30:17,750
but I really want you to catch this.

575
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:20,070
Where are you on those claims?

576
00:30:20,490 --> 00:30:23,860
because we're all going to be held accountable to those claims.

577
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:27,800
And if you're not ready to make that decision, I respect that,

578
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:31,700
but I want you to begin investigating so that you know what you believe and why.

579
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,980
Because it's intellectually dishonest to go out there and just say,

580
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:37,300
well, they all teach the same thing, I don't want to worry about this,

581
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:39,640
because these are eternal issues and they matter.

582
00:30:40,540 --> 00:30:43,140
And friends, I'm here to say, I don't mean to manipulate you emotionally,

583
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:47,540
but we are not in the kind of time in our history where we can just put off these issues.

584
00:30:48,420 --> 00:30:50,920
This is not a time in our nation's history

585
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,840
to just sort of religion doesn't matter

586
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,580
and I'll figure it out some other day.

587
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:55,300
I just like to party.

588
00:30:55,540 --> 00:30:56,820
If that's your attitude today,

589
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:59,140
I want to encourage you to rethink that again.

590
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:02,480
Because I'm really glad given all that's going on

591
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:04,420
that I know Jesus Christ and he's my rock

592
00:31:04,420 --> 00:31:05,380
and I know where I'm going to be

593
00:31:05,380 --> 00:31:07,140
if things go in a whole different direction.

594
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:10,540
And I'm not trying to just pelt you with emotion,

595
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:11,420
but I'm saying, folks,

596
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:13,020
this is a time to get really serious.

597
00:31:13,860 --> 00:31:15,380
And if you were on the fence this morning

598
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:16,780
and you've been kind of here and there

599
00:31:16,780 --> 00:31:18,960
and you know these things are true,

600
00:31:19,060 --> 00:31:20,700
I'm going to ask you this morning to come to Jesus

601
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:23,060
and to get serious with him.

602
00:31:23,950 --> 00:31:24,970
Because he wants you to come.

603
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:26,230
He wants to bring you into his fold.

604
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:27,910
He wants to love you and give you his spirit,

605
00:31:28,230 --> 00:31:29,110
give you eternal life,

606
00:31:29,150 --> 00:31:30,230
and you'll be with him forever.

607
00:31:31,330 --> 00:31:33,730
That's the best news that anybody can ever offer.

608
00:31:36,630 --> 00:31:37,830
And if your will is resistant,

609
00:31:37,950 --> 00:31:39,770
I would just ask you to question why that is.

610
00:31:41,420 --> 00:31:43,780
Because now is the time to get really serious with the Lord.

611
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:45,160
He loves you.

612
00:31:45,700 --> 00:31:46,940
And he wants to give you life.

613
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:48,580
Don't miss it, okay?

614
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:49,660
Don't miss it.

615
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:53,340
And if you have just been loving the Lord Jesus,

616
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:55,380
I hope this message has encouraged you again

617
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,780
and given you a boldness to share that truth to people.

618
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:00,060
Because I'll tell you, our nation is in incredible fear.

619
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,640
We are wrestling with the consequences of ideas.

620
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:04,220
We are wrestling with truth,

621
00:32:04,300 --> 00:32:05,940
and we are wrestling with germs and things

622
00:32:05,940 --> 00:32:07,960
that are taking people out, and it is a scary time.

623
00:32:08,540 --> 00:32:10,020
And I don't know where this is all going to go,

624
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:13,040
but I know it's not a time to just kind of push

625
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:15,900
your thinking about eternal issues off infinitum.

626
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:19,060
And I would just encourage you to wrestle with Jesus,

627
00:32:19,060 --> 00:32:22,220
the way and the truth and the life.

